WEBVTT

00:05.689 --> 00:07.160
Green.

00:07.220 --> 00:09.130
That's what I
remember the most:

00:09.190 --> 00:11.660
that shade of green.

00:11.730 --> 00:14.730
It might have been
the most beautiful thing

00:14.800 --> 00:17.970
I had ever seen.

00:18.030 --> 00:20.600
Just the color.

00:20.670 --> 00:22.510
The only time we were inside
was when we slept,

00:22.570 --> 00:25.780
and even then
not half the time.

00:25.840 --> 00:28.650
There was a tire swing.

00:32.320 --> 00:34.580
Every summer,
that thing would break,

00:34.650 --> 00:37.250
and every summer,
Grandpa would fix it.

00:45.760 --> 00:50.000
And the apples--
Oh, man, I'm telling you,

00:50.070 --> 00:51.570
apples ain't the same
anymore.

00:51.640 --> 00:54.040
I mean,
I don't know what they--

00:54.100 --> 00:56.240
Pete, would you shut
the hell up?

00:56.310 --> 00:58.180
Nothing's the same anymore.

00:58.240 --> 01:00.610
Lights out!

01:00.680 --> 01:02.650
Three years in here.

01:03.950 --> 01:06.050
I feel like I've spent
every moment of that

01:06.150 --> 01:07.150
listening to this crap.

01:07.220 --> 01:09.050
Pete had the perfect summers.

01:09.150 --> 01:11.160
Pete had the perfect
grandparents.

01:11.190 --> 01:12.720
All that money
from the bond business,

01:12.790 --> 01:15.160
but they loved you anyways.
They had the time for you,

01:15.190 --> 01:16.790
until Mommy pissed them off
20 years ago.

01:16.860 --> 01:19.160
They did.

01:19.230 --> 01:22.330
It's all true.
And it just pisses you off

01:22.400 --> 01:24.530
because it was better
than your screwed-up life,

01:24.600 --> 01:25.740
whatever that was.

01:25.800 --> 01:29.940
I know your life sucked
worse than mine.

01:30.010 --> 01:31.810
At least
I have people skills.

01:31.880 --> 01:33.880
You're a con man.

01:33.940 --> 01:35.280
Yes, I'm a confidence man.

01:35.350 --> 01:37.180
I give people confidence,
they give me their money.

01:37.250 --> 01:40.180
You, what, you tried to rob
a gun range at gunpoint?

01:40.220 --> 01:42.490
I get out of here in two days.

01:42.550 --> 01:44.450
You're not even up for parole
for another two years,

01:44.520 --> 01:48.230
which means my life is
currently better than yours.

01:48.290 --> 01:49.590
So I either had
a better life than you,

01:49.660 --> 01:52.700
or none of that crap
means nothing.

01:55.570 --> 01:58.340
Either way,
just stop talking about it.

01:59.800 --> 02:01.540
Okay?

02:05.240 --> 02:07.480
24 more hours, Eddie.

02:07.540 --> 02:09.710
Oh, my God. You know
the first thing I'm gonna do?

02:09.780 --> 02:11.820
I'm gonna murder
a cheeseburger at Donovan's.

02:11.880 --> 02:13.420
Yeah, that's a good burger.

02:13.480 --> 02:15.650
All right, little brother,
I'll see you tomorrow, okay?

02:15.720 --> 02:17.120
Uh...

02:17.220 --> 02:18.220
Everything all right?

02:18.290 --> 02:20.360
No, Marius, it's not.

02:20.420 --> 02:23.790
Uh...you can't come back here.

02:23.860 --> 02:25.300
- What do you mean?
- It's Vince.

02:25.360 --> 02:27.030
We owe him more money
than I thought--

02:27.100 --> 02:28.830
- A lot more.
- How much?

02:30.100 --> 02:31.640
- A hundred grand.
- What?

02:31.700 --> 02:34.340
Wait a minute. That's
what it was to start with.

02:34.400 --> 02:35.910
I've been paying him.
You've been paying him.

02:35.970 --> 02:37.810
- What the fuck happened?
- He says it's interest

02:37.870 --> 02:40.710
that the-- the vig's been
running for three years.

02:40.780 --> 02:44.380
- So now you tell me? I mean--
- I just found out.

02:47.120 --> 02:48.350
He wants me dead, doesn't he?

02:48.420 --> 02:50.550
I don't know. I don't know.

02:50.620 --> 02:52.460
But he's gonna have people
waiting for you

02:52.520 --> 02:53.520
when you get out, so--

02:53.590 --> 02:54.890
Well, I got to talk to him.

02:54.960 --> 02:57.690
No. I think this is
beyond talk, Marius,

02:57.760 --> 02:59.100
at least for you.

02:59.160 --> 03:00.530
Look, he likes me, all right?

03:00.600 --> 03:03.100
So just--
Let me try to work him.

03:03.170 --> 03:04.630
But right now you got to hide.

03:04.700 --> 03:06.640
- Ah, Eddie.
- You got to hide.

03:08.000 --> 03:10.310
Yeah. All right. All right.

